{
  "items": [
    {
      "allowLineSplit": true,
      "content": "Writing Systems of the World",
      "keepWithNext": true,
      "kind": "flow-block",
      "overflowPolicy": "clip",
      "pageBreakBefore": false,
      "source": {
        "path": "elements[0]"
      },
      "sourceType": "h1",
      "style": {
        "fontSize": 24,
        "fontWeight": "bold",
        "keepWithNext": true,
        "marginBottom": 18
      }
    },
    {
      "allowLineSplit": true,
      "content": "Human writing has taken dozens of independent forms over five millennia. Each script reflects a specific relationship between sound, symbol, and direction. This document exercises the engine across the major script families: Latin, CJK ideographs, Arabic abjad, Thai abugida, Hangul syllabic blocks, and the combining-mark structures that connect them all.",
      "keepWithNext": false,
      "kind": "flow-block",
      "overflowPolicy": "clip",
      "pageBreakBefore": false,
      "source": {
        "path": "elements[1]"
      },
      "sourceType": "p",
      "style": {
        "allowLineSplit": true,
        "marginBottom": 12,
        "orphans": 2,
        "widows": 2
      }
    },
    {
      "allowLineSplit": true,
      "content": "Latin — Combining Marks & Extended Characters",
      "keepWithNext": true,
      "kind": "flow-block",
      "overflowPolicy": "clip",
      "pageBreakBefore": false,
      "source": {
        "path": "elements[2]"
      },
      "sourceType": "h2",
      "style": {
        "fontSize": 18,
        "fontWeight": "bold",
        "keepWithNext": true,
        "marginBottom": 10,
        "marginTop": 12
      }
    },
    {
      "allowLineSplit": true,
      "content": "Acute, grave, and circumflex accents attach as zero-width combining marks above their base letters: á ë ô ñ ṣ. Stacked forms arise when two accents modify a single glyph: ñ́. Each of these sequences must be measured as a single grapheme cluster — splitting on a combining mark boundary is a rendering error.",
      "keepWithNext": false,
      "kind": "flow-block",
      "overflowPolicy": "clip",
      "pageBreakBefore": false,
      "source": {
        "path": "elements[3]"
      },
      "sourceType": "p",
      "style": {
        "allowLineSplit": true,
        "marginBottom": 12,
        "orphans": 2,
        "widows": 2
      }
    },
    {
      "allowLineSplit": true,
      "content": "East European and Vietnamese extensions cover a wider range of diacritics: ă ắ ặ ổ ẽ ư ứ ự. Extended Latin-B adds historical and phonetic forms: ȅ ȃ ȏ ȗ — all of them within the Arimo and Noto Sans coverage area.",
      "keepWithNext": false,
      "kind": "flow-block",
      "overflowPolicy": "clip",
      "pageBreakBefore": false,
      "source": {
        "path": "elements[4]"
      },
      "sourceType": "p",
      "style": {
        "allowLineSplit": true,
        "marginBottom": 12,
        "orphans": 2,
        "widows": 2
      }
    },
    {
      "allowLineSplit": true,
      "content": "CJK — Chinese, Japanese, Korean",
      "keepWithNext": true,
      "kind": "flow-block",
      "overflowPolicy": "clip",
      "pageBreakBefore": false,
      "source": {
        "path": "elements[5]"
      },
      "sourceType": "h2",
      "style": {
        "fontSize": 18,
        "fontWeight": "bold",
        "keepWithNext": true,
        "marginBottom": 10,
        "marginTop": 12
      }
    },
    {
      "allowLineSplit": true,
      "content": "汉字 (Hànzì) — Chinese characters used for Mandarin, Cantonese, and classical texts: 天地玄黄，宇宙洪荒。日月盈昃，辰宿列张。寒来暑往，秋收冬藏。闰余成岁，律吕调阳。",
      "keepWithNext": false,
      "kind": "flow-block",
      "overflowPolicy": "clip",
      "pageBreakBefore": false,
      "source": {
        "path": "elements[6]"
      },
      "sourceType": "p",
      "style": {
        "allowLineSplit": true,
        "marginBottom": 12,
        "orphans": 2,
        "widows": 2
      }
    },
    {
      "allowLineSplit": true,
      "content": "日本語 (Nihongo) — Japanese mixes kanji with hiragana and katakana syllabaries: 春はあけぼの。やうやう白くなりゆく山ぎは、少し明かりて、紫だちたる雲の細くたなびきたる。",
      "keepWithNext": false,
      "kind": "flow-block",
      "overflowPolicy": "clip",
      "pageBreakBefore": false,
      "source": {
        "path": "elements[7]"
      },
      "sourceType": "p",
      "style": {
        "allowLineSplit": true,
        "marginBottom": 12,
        "orphans": 2,
        "widows": 2
      }
    },
    {
      "allowLineSplit": true,
      "content": "한국어 (Hangugeo) — Korean Hangul syllable blocks, each composed from jamo consonant and vowel units: 이 문서는 다양한 스크립트 시스템이 단일 레이아웃 엔진에서 올바르게 렌더링되는지를 확인합니다. 줄 바꿈과 자간이 안정적이어야 합니다.",
      "keepWithNext": false,
      "kind": "flow-block",
      "overflowPolicy": "clip",
      "pageBreakBefore": false,
      "source": {
        "path": "elements[8]"
      },
      "sourceType": "p",
      "style": {
        "allowLineSplit": true,
        "marginBottom": 12,
        "orphans": 2,
        "widows": 2
      }
    },
    {
      "allowLineSplit": true,
      "content": "Variation selectors change glyph form without changing Unicode identity: 漢︀字 uses a variation-selector sequence. Such sequences must not be split across segments.",
      "keepWithNext": false,
      "kind": "flow-block",
      "overflowPolicy": "clip",
      "pageBreakBefore": false,
      "source": {
        "path": "elements[9]"
      },
      "sourceType": "p",
      "style": {
        "allowLineSplit": true,
        "marginBottom": 12,
        "orphans": 2,
        "widows": 2
      }
    },
    {
      "allowLineSplit": true,
      "content": "Arabic — Right-to-Left Shaping",
      "keepWithNext": true,
      "kind": "flow-block",
      "overflowPolicy": "clip",
      "pageBreakBefore": false,
      "source": {
        "path": "elements[10]"
      },
      "sourceType": "h2",
      "style": {
        "fontSize": 18,
        "fontWeight": "bold",
        "keepWithNext": true,
        "marginBottom": 10,
        "marginTop": 12
      }
    },
    {
      "allowLineSplit": true,
      "content": "اللغة العربية — Arabic is written right to left. Letters change shape depending on their position within a word (initial, medial, final, or isolated): بِسْمِ اللَّهِ الرَّحْمَٰنِ الرَّحِيمِ.",
      "keepWithNext": false,
      "kind": "flow-block",
      "overflowPolicy": "clip",
      "pageBreakBefore": false,
      "source": {
        "path": "elements[11]"
      },
      "sourceType": "p",
      "style": {
        "allowLineSplit": true,
        "direction": "rtl",
        "fontFamily": "Noto Sans Arabic",
        "marginBottom": 12,
        "orphans": 2,
        "widows": 2
      }
    },
    {
      "allowLineSplit": true,
      "content": "Mixing scripts in a single paragraph — a common requirement in multilingual publishing: The word للنشر means \"for publishing\" and مرحباً means \"welcome\". Bidirectional text must resolve direction per-run and align glyphs from the correct edge.",
      "keepWithNext": false,
      "kind": "flow-block",
      "overflowPolicy": "clip",
      "pageBreakBefore": false,
      "source": {
        "path": "elements[12]"
      },
      "sourceType": "p",
      "style": {
        "allowLineSplit": true,
        "marginBottom": 12,
        "orphans": 2,
        "widows": 2
      }
    },
    {
      "allowLineSplit": true,
      "content": "Thai — Abugida with Stacked Vowels",
      "keepWithNext": true,
      "kind": "flow-block",
      "overflowPolicy": "clip",
      "pageBreakBefore": false,
      "source": {
        "path": "elements[13]"
      },
      "sourceType": "h2",
      "style": {
        "fontSize": 18,
        "fontWeight": "bold",
        "keepWithNext": true,
        "marginBottom": 10,
        "marginTop": 12
      }
    },
    {
      "allowLineSplit": true,
      "content": "ภาษาไทย — Thai is written left to right without spaces between words. Vowel signs appear above, below, before, and after their consonant base: ก้า กำ เกิด กับ ผู้ใช้. Tone marks stack above vowel marks: ก้ ก่ ก๊ ก๋. Each cluster must be measured as one indivisible unit.",
      "keepWithNext": false,
      "kind": "flow-block",
      "overflowPolicy": "clip",
      "pageBreakBefore": false,
      "source": {
        "path": "elements[14]"
      },
      "sourceType": "p",
      "style": {
        "allowLineSplit": true,
        "marginBottom": 12,
        "orphans": 2,
        "widows": 2
      }
    },
    {
      "allowLineSplit": true,
      "content": "สวัสดีครับ — A standard Thai greeting, usefully representative of the typical glyph-stack density. The phrase ขอบคุณมาก (\"thank you very much\") follows: every syllable carries at least one diacritic mark above or below the base consonant.",
      "keepWithNext": false,
      "kind": "flow-block",
      "overflowPolicy": "clip",
      "pageBreakBefore": false,
      "source": {
        "path": "elements[15]"
      },
      "sourceType": "p",
      "style": {
        "allowLineSplit": true,
        "marginBottom": 12,
        "orphans": 2,
        "widows": 2
      }
    },
    {
      "allowLineSplit": true,
      "content": "Dense Mixed-Script Lines",
      "keepWithNext": true,
      "kind": "flow-block",
      "overflowPolicy": "clip",
      "pageBreakBefore": false,
      "source": {
        "path": "elements[16]"
      },
      "sourceType": "h2",
      "style": {
        "fontSize": 18,
        "fontWeight": "bold",
        "keepWithNext": true,
        "marginBottom": 10,
        "marginTop": 12
      }
    },
    {
      "allowLineSplit": true,
      "content": "Latin A/B test 你好 こんにちは 한국어 สวัสดี مرحبا — punctuation !? ；，。 symbols ★☆✓ and variation sequence 漢︀字.",
      "keepWithNext": false,
      "kind": "flow-block",
      "overflowPolicy": "clip",
      "pageBreakBefore": false,
      "source": {
        "path": "elements[17]"
      },
      "sourceType": "p",
      "style": {
        "allowLineSplit": true,
        "marginBottom": 12,
        "orphans": 2,
        "widows": 2
      }
    },
    {
      "allowLineSplit": true,
      "content": "This paragraph forces wraps while mixing scripts in high density: English + 中文 + 日本語 + 한국어 + ภาษาไทย + العربية with punctuation clusters (—, …, 、, 。, ؟) and symbols (∑, ≤, ≥, ∞). Repeat for stability: English + 中文 + 日本語 + 한국어 + ภาษาไทย + العربية.",
      "keepWithNext": false,
      "kind": "flow-block",
      "overflowPolicy": "clip",
      "pageBreakBefore": false,
      "source": {
        "path": "elements[18]"
      },
      "sourceType": "p",
      "style": {
        "allowLineSplit": true,
        "marginBottom": 12,
        "orphans": 2,
        "widows": 2
      }
    },
    {
      "allowLineSplit": true,
      "content": "Grapheme Cluster Stress",
      "keepWithNext": true,
      "kind": "flow-block",
      "overflowPolicy": "clip",
      "pageBreakBefore": false,
      "source": {
        "path": "elements[19]"
      },
      "sourceType": "h2",
      "style": {
        "fontSize": 18,
        "fontWeight": "bold",
        "keepWithNext": true,
        "marginBottom": 10,
        "marginTop": 12
      }
    },
    {
      "allowLineSplit": true,
      "content": "Zero-width joiners and variation sequences at segment boundaries: ☺‍☻, ♀‍♂, 漢︀字 wrapped in text. Each joined sequence must survive line-breaking without being torn apart at the ZWJ or VS codepoint.",
      "keepWithNext": false,
      "kind": "flow-block",
      "overflowPolicy": "clip",
      "pageBreakBefore": false,
      "source": {
        "path": "elements[20]"
      },
      "sourceType": "p",
      "style": {
        "allowLineSplit": true,
        "marginBottom": 12,
        "orphans": 2,
        "widows": 2
      }
    },
    {
      "allowLineSplit": true,
      "content": "Combining marks that stack: q̈ (q + combining diaeresis), Z̧ (Z + combining cedilla below), ẇ (w + combining dot above). These test that grapheme width is measured on the composed form, not the base character alone.",
      "keepWithNext": false,
      "kind": "flow-block",
      "overflowPolicy": "clip",
      "pageBreakBefore": false,
      "source": {
        "path": "elements[21]"
      },
      "sourceType": "p",
      "style": {
        "allowLineSplit": true,
        "marginBottom": 12,
        "orphans": 2,
        "widows": 2
      }
    },
    {
      "allowLineSplit": true,
      "content": "Unicode Standard §3.6: A grapheme cluster is an approximation to what a user considers to be a character. The engine must treat each cluster as atomic for measurement, line-breaking, and cursor placement.",
      "keepWithNext": false,
      "kind": "flow-block",
      "overflowPolicy": "clip",
      "pageBreakBefore": false,
      "source": {
        "path": "elements[22]"
      },
      "sourceType": "blockquote",
